00:12:13.549 --> 00:12:15.217
<i>He started making
inappropriate comments.</i>

250
00:12:15.301 --> 00:12:17.175
[sighs] <i>and then. on a
number of occasions.</i>

251
00:12:17.259 --> 00:12:18.835
<i>he tried to persuade
me to sleep with him.'</i>

252
00:12:18.919 --> 00:12:21.669
<i>Ellery describes an incident
at Williams College:</i>

253
00:12:21.753 --> 00:12:24.868
'Noah had punched out the
school newspaper's book critic

254
00:12:24.952 --> 00:12:26.556
for giving <i>Descent</i> a bad review.'"

255
00:12:26.640 --> 00:12:27.855
- Okay. Wait a minute.
- [engine stops]

256
00:12:27.939 --> 00:12:31.186
Did this really happen?
Did you punch a kid?

257
00:12:31.270 --> 00:12:34.536
No. no. He was. like. 22. and
he absolutely deserved it.

258
00:12:34.620 --> 00:12:37.093
"'The story was going viral.

259
00:12:37.177 --> 00:12:39.377
We needed to strategize about
how to run interference.

260
00:12:39.461 --> 00:12:41.621
and Noah insisted his hotel
room was the only place

261
00:12:41.705 --> 00:12:43.245
- private enough to talk.'"
- Great.

262
00:12:43.329 --> 00:12:45.803
"'When I arrived. I could tell
immediately that he was drunk.

263
00:12:45.887 --> 00:12:47.666
He pulled me into his
room. started kissing me.

264
00:12:47.750 --> 00:12:48.876
- groping me.'"
- Seriously?

265
00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:50.472
Helen. this is not what happened.

266
00:12:50.556 --> 00:12:52.796
- She was throwing herself at me.
- Great.

267
00:12:52.880 --> 00:12:54.451
[sighs] Shit. I lost my place.

268
00:12:54.535 --> 00:12:57.009
Just give me the fucking thing.

269
00:12:57.093 --> 00:12:58.530
I didn't sleep with her. Helen.

270
00:12:58.614 --> 00:13:00.238
I know it sounds crazy. but
I think she's doing this

271
00:13:00.322 --> 00:13:02.366
- as some kind of revenge.
- Yeah. that does sound crazy.

272
00:13:02.450 --> 00:13:03.899
[phone chiming]

273
00:13:03.983 --> 00:13:06.345
Now my agent is saying I-I
should release a statement

274
00:13:06.429 --> 00:13:09.353
saying that I respect women and
apologize to those I hurt.

275
00:13:09.437 --> 00:13:10.943
- Great. Do that.
- Yeah. but my publisher's

276
00:13:11.027 --> 00:13:14.349
threatening to exercise a
morality clause in my contract.

277
00:13:14.433 --> 00:13:16.195
- A morality clause?
- Yeah.

278
00:13:16.279 --> 00:13:17.404
And not publish my book

279
00:13:17.488 --> 00:13:19.083
if all this negative
publicity continues.

280
00:13:19.167 --> 00:13:20.378
Oh. my God. What are they waiting for?

281
00:13:20.462 --> 00:13:22.243
And then Gottlief says I
shouldn't do anything.

282
00:13:22.327 --> 00:13:24.752
because he thinks there's
potential for a civil suit.

283
00:13:25.496 --> 00:13:26.747
What should I do?

284
00:13:26.831 --> 00:13:28.249
I don't know!

285
00:13:28.333 --> 00:13:29.250
[ringtone playing]

286
00:13:29.334 --> 00:13:30.626
Just shut off your phone!

287
00:13:30.710 --> 00:13:32.879
It's not mine. It's yours.

288
00:13:35.006 --> 00:13:36.882
Shit.

289
00:13:36.966 --> 00:13:39.343
It's my boss.

290
00:13:39.428 --> 00:13:40.897
Amy. hi.

291
00:13:40.982 --> 00:13:44.150
Um. yeah. I might just be
running a teeny bit late.

292
00:13:44.235 --> 00:13:45.862
But...

293
00:13:48.169 --> 00:13:49.254
Why's that?

294
00:13:53.269 --> 00:13:54.566
Oh.

295
00:13:54.650 --> 00:13:56.610
Yeah. No. he is... he is my...

296
00:13:56.694 --> 00:13:59.238
uh. my ex-husband.

297
00:14:06.892 --> 00:14:08.179
Okay. makes sense.

298
00:14:10.637 --> 00:14:12.001
Thanks. You. too.

299
00:14:12.376 --> 00:14:13.503
[phone clicks]

300
00:14:15.467 --> 00:14:17.631
[clicks tongue] Well. that's a record.

301
00:14:17.715 --> 00:14:19.967
I got fired before I started my job.

302
00:14:20.051 --> 00:14:21.844
[sighs]

303
00:14:21.928 --> 00:14:23.429
'Cause of me?

304
00:14:23.513 --> 00:14:25.264
[Sierra] Hi.

305
00:14:25.348 --> 00:14:26.724
Hi.

306
00:14:27.649 --> 00:14:28.939
Everything okay?

307
00:14:33.231 --> 00:14:34.690
Yeah. it's fine.

308
00:14:34.774 --> 00:14:36.608
[phone ringing]

309
00:14:36.692 --> 00:14:38.444
Fuck. it's the kids' school.

310
00:14:38.528 --> 00:14:40.237
Hello?

311
00:14:40.321 --> 00:14:41.321
Yeah.

312
00:14:42.738 --> 00:14:44.490
He did what?

313
00:14:46.025 --> 00:14:47.554
Sure. Yeah. I'll-I'll...

314
00:14:47.639 --> 00:14:48.886
I'll come right over.

315
00:14:48.971 --> 00:14:50.054
Soon as I can. Thanks.

316
00:14:51.079 --> 00:14:52.287
Trevor got in a fight.

317
00:14:52.372 --> 00:14:54.001
- Oh. my God. Is he okay?
- They didn't give any detail.

318
00:14:54.085 --> 00:14:56.387
They just told me to
come and pick him up.

319
00:14:56.472 --> 00:14:57.654
No. I'm going.

320
00:14:57.739 --> 00:14:59.339
Yeah. Helen. the school called me.

321
00:14:59.423 --> 00:15:01.247
Yes. because it was probably your fault.

322
00:15:01.332 --> 00:15:03.594
Please. That may be true. but
it's really important to me

323
00:15:03.678 --> 00:15:05.459
to get to him. to talk
to him. to explain.

324
00:15:05.543 --> 00:15:06.906
Well. that's not happening.

325
00:15:08.099 --> 00:15:09.349
[slow. somber music]

326
00:15:09.433 --> 00:15:12.269
<i>♪♪♪</i>

327
00:15:12.353 --> 00:15:15.106
[siren wailing faintly in distance]

328
00:15:22.696 --> 00:15:24.496
I'm sorry about the job.

329
00:15:32.832 --> 00:15:35.293
I worked my ass off for that job.

330
00:15:38.477 --> 00:15:40.947
I didn't go to Montauk to
plan my daughter's wedding

331
00:15:41.031 --> 00:15:42.213
to get that job.

332
00:15:42.297 --> 00:15:43.759
Do you know how painful that was for me?

333
00:15:44.760 --> 00:15:46.403
But doesn't matter. really.

334
00:15:46.487 --> 00:15:47.830
'cause you know what?

335
00:15:47.914 --> 00:15:49.515
No matter how hard I work.

336
00:15:49.599 --> 00:15:52.237
you always manage to find
a way to fuck my shit up.

337
00:15:52.321 --> 00:15:54.509
- I said I was sorry.
- Well. if you want to apologize.

338
00:15:54.593 --> 00:15:56.239
why don't you start with those women?

339
00:15:57.646 --> 00:16:00.484
How can I apologize. Helen.
when I didn't do anything?

340
00:16:00.568 --> 00:16:02.165
Oh. really? So they're all lying?

341
00:16:02.249 --> 00:16:03.695
- Why would they do that?
- I don't know.

342
00:16:03.779 --> 00:16:05.239
That's what I'm trying to figure out.

343
00:16:05.323 --> 00:16:07.033
Oh. so you didn't sleep
with the student teacher?

344
00:16:08.358 --> 00:16:10.202
It was... it was consensual.

345
00:16:10.286 --> 00:16:12.454
Oh. except you were her boss!

346
00:16:12.538 --> 00:16:15.349
So maybe it didn't feel
consensual to her.

347
00:16:16.431 --> 00:16:18.522
[groans] And what about Eden?

348
00:16:18.899 --> 00:16:21.547
She came to my room. uninvited.
and we made out for maybe

349
00:16:21.631 --> 00:16:22.845
fucking one minute. That was it.

350
00:16:22.929 --> 00:16:24.032
But why did you let her in?

351
00:16:24.116 --> 00:16:26.245
Did you think maybe that
might have been a bad idea?

352
00:16:26.329 --> 00:16:28.337
- Because I was drunk.
- Well. whose fault is that?

353
00:16:28.421 --> 00:16:30.588
- Yours. actually! Yes.
- What?

354
00:16:30.672 --> 00:16:31.978
Earlier in the night. we went out.

355
00:16:32.062 --> 00:16:33.267
As usual. you were drinking like a fish.

356
00:16:33.351 --> 00:16:35.727
You got me shit-faced. That
was why I didn't kick her out

357
00:16:35.811 --> 00:16:36.728
- immediately!
- Are you seriously trying

358
00:16:36.812 --> 00:16:38.230
to turn this around on me?

359
00:16:38.314 --> 00:16:40.365
Your inability to take responsibility

360
00:16:40.449 --> 00:16:41.911
for your actions is pathological.

361
00:16:41.995 --> 00:16:44.069
- Oh. really? Really?!
- Yeah. Yeah.

362
00:16:44.153 --> 00:16:47.030
Well. maybe 'cause I'm so busy
taking responsibility for yours!

363
00:16:47.114 --> 00:16:49.741
Oh. my God. Fuck you!

364
00:16:49.825 --> 00:16:51.827
[slow. somber music]

365
00:16:51.911 --> 00:16:53.579
<i>♪♪♪</i>

366
00:16:58.521 --> 00:17:01.729
I've done time for a crime I
didn't commit already. Helen.

367
00:17:02.244 --> 00:17:03.662
I'm not doing it again.

368
00:17:04.340 --> 00:17:06.259
[siren wailing in distance]

369
00:17:07.802 --> 00:17:09.595
[indistinct police radio chatter]

370
00:17:09.679 --> 00:17:11.472
[horns honking]

371
00:17:15.184 --> 00:17:18.162
- Excuse me. What's going on?
- They're shutting down Sunset

372
00:17:18.246 --> 00:17:20.189
to help with evacuations off the 405.

373
00:17:20.273 --> 00:17:21.607
You got to pull off
here and turn around.

374
00:17:21.692 --> 00:17:24.175
No. I have to go to Brentwood
to get my kids at school.

375
00:17:25.486 --> 00:17:27.029
What do you mean? I have to get through.

376
00:17:27.113 --> 00:17:28.530
They're about to start
evacuating the schools

377
00:17:28.614 --> 00:17:30.250
- in Brentwood anyway.
- Well. if they're evacuating

378
00:17:30.334 --> 00:17:32.092
the schools. then I really
need to get through

379
00:17:32.176 --> 00:17:34.286
so I can. you know.
evacuate my children.

380
00:17:34.370 --> 00:17:35.662
Ma'am. I can't let you through.

381
00:17:35.746 --> 00:17:37.610
Dude. what the fuck is your problem?

382
00:17:37.694 --> 00:17:38.916
- Helen.
- My kids are over there.

383
00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:40.709
- Helen. Helen. this is...
- I have to go get them.

384
00:17:40.793 --> 00:17:42.133
This isn't helping. Come on.

385
00:17:42.217 --> 00:17:43.566
We'll figure something else out.

386
00:17:43.650 --> 00:17:45.839
I'm sorry. okay? I am.

387
00:17:45.923 --> 00:17:47.216
Let's just go.

388
00:17:53.601 --> 00:17:55.129
Can you call Trevor?

389
00:18:02.566 --> 00:18:03.691
Voice mail.

390
00:18:08.154 --> 00:18:10.197
- Fuck. Stacey. too.
- What?

391
00:18:10.281 --> 00:18:12.500
Do we know anyone on the
Westside who could pick 'em up?

392
00:18:12.584 --> 00:18:14.993
Um...

393
00:18:15.077 --> 00:18:16.268
Yeah.

394
00:18:16.352 --> 00:18:17.872
Uh. Brooklyn's mom.

395
00:18:18.789 --> 00:18:20.426
[line ringing]

396
00:18:21.117 --> 00:18:22.418
Good idea.

397
00:18:24.587 --> 00:18:26.533
Um. I'll pack a bag for the kids

398
00:18:26.617 --> 00:18:27.798
in case we can't get back over here.

399
00:18:27.882 --> 00:18:29.668
Can you call Whitney. see
what's up with her flight?

400
00:18:29.752 --> 00:18:31.677
Yeah. I'll check in with Martin. too.

401
00:18:31.761 --> 00:18:33.512
- [Eddie fussing]
- [Priya talking playfully]

402
00:18:33.596 --> 00:18:34.826
Priya.

403
00:18:34.910 --> 00:18:36.286
Oh. hi.

404
00:18:36.370 --> 00:18:39.656
Isn't he the most beautiful
baby you've ever seen?

405
00:18:39.740 --> 00:18:42.924
Yeah... he is beautiful.
yeah. Where's Sierra?

406
00:18:43.008 --> 00:18:45.618
- [phone ringing]
- Sierra is packing.

407
00:18:45.702 --> 00:18:47.609
- Hi.
- [Noah] Hello?

408
00:18:47.693 --> 00:18:49.361
- Hi.
- Um. sorry.

409
00:18:49.445 --> 00:18:51.945
Uh. it was starting to
smell like smoke up here.

410
00:18:52.029 --> 00:18:53.879
I wanted to get Eddie out of the hills.

411
00:18:53.963 --> 00:18:55.005
I didn't want to bother you guys.

412
00:18:55.089 --> 00:18:57.195
'cause you seemed kind of
busy. so I called Priya.

413
00:18:57.279 --> 00:18:59.621
- Oh.
- [Priya] They're going to stay

414
00:18:59.705 --> 00:19:02.487
with Abdul and me until
the smoke clears.

415
00:19:02.571 --> 00:19:04.247
For as long as they like.

416
00:19:04.331 --> 00:19:07.103
The boy should get to
know his grandparents.

417
00:19:08.464 --> 00:19:09.853
Thank you.

418
00:19:09.937 --> 00:19:11.801
Mm-hmm. I'll wait outside.

419
00:19:11.885 --> 00:19:13.969
Okay. Be safe.

420
00:19:14.053 --> 00:19:16.222
[sirens wailing. helicopters
whirring in distance]

421
00:19:18.641 --> 00:19:19.975
[door closes]

422
00:19:25.261 --> 00:19:26.929
[door closes]

423
00:19:27.014 --> 00:19:28.307
What's wrong?

424
00:19:29.360 --> 00:19:33.447
Uh. they're changing
the name of my movie.

425
00:19:33.531 --> 00:19:34.800
Who is?

426
00:19:34.884 --> 00:19:36.856
The producers of <i>Descent.</i> They're...

427
00:19:37.956 --> 00:19:39.742
They're changing the
title to something else.

428
00:19:39.826 --> 00:19:42.609
and they're offering me a buyout
to take my name off the credits.

429
00:19:43.359 --> 00:19:45.543
So... they're erasing
me from my own story.

430
00:19:56.282 --> 00:19:57.714
I'm sorry.

431
00:20:01.225 --> 00:20:03.227
[ringtone playing]

432
00:20:06.313 --> 00:20:07.666
It's Lauren.

433
00:20:07.750 --> 00:20:09.348
Hey. Lauren. what's...

434
00:20:11.235 --> 00:20:12.653
What do you mean?

435
00:20:14.697 --> 00:20:16.691
Well. where did they go? I... Yeah.

436
00:20:17.342 --> 00:20:19.744
Okay. I gotta... Yeah. Of course.

437
00:20:19.828 --> 00:20:21.048
Uh. bye.

438
00:20:21.132 --> 00:20:23.789
Um. Trevor and Stacey weren't at school.

439
00:20:23.873 --> 00:20:25.165
What? Where are they?

440
00:20:25.249 --> 00:20:27.347
I don't know. Brooklyn said
someone else picked them up.

441
00:20:27.431 --> 00:20:28.460
but he doesn't know who.

442
00:20:28.544 --> 00:20:30.212
Okay. I'll call Trevor. you call Stacey.

443
00:20:30.296 --> 00:20:32.798
[line ringing]

444
00:20:36.552 --> 00:20:39.234
- It's just a voice mail.
- It's just ringing.

445
00:20:39.318 --> 00:20:40.833
I don't understand. Where would they go?

446
00:20:40.917 --> 00:20:42.370
The school wouldn't
have let them just go.

447
00:20:42.455 --> 00:20:44.768
Well. they're teenagers. They
can go when they want to go.

448
00:20:44.852 --> 00:20:47.270
I don't... I don't un... I
mean. no one's texted me.

449
00:20:47.354 --> 00:20:48.730
Anyone else who could
have picked them up?

450
00:20:48.814 --> 00:20:50.133
I don't know. I mean. I-I-I don't...

451
00:20:50.217 --> 00:20:53.973
I have this. um... the-the
tracking app thingy.

452
00:20:54.057 --> 00:20:54.986
I don't... Can you do that?

453
00:20:55.070 --> 00:20:56.863
- Let me see.
- I've never used it.

454
00:20:56.947 --> 00:20:58.899
- Okay. it's finding Trevor.
- Okay.

455
00:21:00.914 --> 00:21:02.373
That's weird.

456
00:21:02.458 --> 00:21:04.251
- What is?
- Why is he in Malibu?

457
00:21:07.032 --> 00:21:08.919
- Oh. my God.
- What?

458
00:21:11.545 --> 00:21:13.047
They're at Sasha's.

459
00:21:14.089 --> 00:21:15.732
I mean. what the fuck?

460
00:21:15.816 --> 00:21:18.260
[phone clicking]

461
00:21:18.344 --> 00:21:19.720
[line ringing]

462
00:21:19.804 --> 00:21:21.805
Hi. Do you have my kids?

463
00:21:21.889 --> 00:21:23.515
[phone ringing]

464
00:21:23.599 --> 00:21:27.636
No. I don't want to FaceTime.
I don't want to FaceTime.

465
00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:31.690
<i>Hey. hey. I just want you to
see that your kids are fine.</i>

466
00:21:31.774 --> 00:21:33.191
<i>They're happy. safe.</i>

467
00:21:33.275 --> 00:21:34.700
<i>Look. Hey. kids. say hi to your mother.</i>

468
00:21:34.784 --> 00:21:36.040
Hi. guys.

469
00:21:36.124 --> 00:21:37.863
- Look. Sasha.
<i>- Yes?</i>

470
00:21:37.947 --> 00:21:40.532
You cannot just get my fucking
kids without telling me.

471
00:21:40.616 --> 00:21:42.329
<i>I tried calling you.</i>

472
00:21:42.413 --> 00:21:44.390
<i>but your phone kept going
straight to voice mail.</i>

473
00:21:44.474 --> 00:21:45.871
<i>Listen. the city's gridlocked.</i>

474
00:21:45.955 --> 00:21:48.188
<i>and-and I'm sending over a helicopter.</i>

475
00:21:48.272 --> 00:21:49.628
You're sending a helicopter where?

476
00:21:49.712 --> 00:21:50.417
<i>To get you.</i>

477
00:21:50.501 --> 00:21:52.043
<i>Yeah. I've-I've checked
it with my security guys.</i>

478
00:21:52.127 --> 00:21:53.550
<i>There's a landing pad just up the...</i>

479
00:21:53.634 --> 00:21:54.838
<i>the hill from your house.</i>

480
00:21:54.922 --> 00:21:56.298
Yeah. I can't... I can't do that.

481
00:21:56.382 --> 00:21:57.924
I have a house full of people.

482
00:21:58.008 --> 00:21:59.217
[laughs] <i>Of course you do.</i>

483
00:21:59.301 --> 00:22:01.341
<i>What else is new? So. who's there?</i>

484
00:22:01.425 --> 00:22:02.763
<i>Perhaps we can squeeze them in. too.</i>

485
00:22:02.847 --> 00:22:04.065
Go. Be with the kids.

486
00:22:05.307 --> 00:22:07.200
<i>- Is that Noah?</i>
- Yes!

487
00:22:07.284 --> 00:22:08.768
<i>What the fuck is he doing there?</i>

488
00:22:08.852 --> 00:22:10.562
<i>Helen. have you... have
you watched the news?</i>

489
00:22:10.646 --> 00:22:12.295
<i>Have you seen what
he's being accused of?</i>

490
00:22:12.379 --> 00:22:14.566
Yeah. that's why he's here. Sasha.

491
00:22:14.650 --> 00:22:17.110
so we can figure out how
to deal with our children.

492
00:22:17.194 --> 00:22:19.279
<i>I just told you. your kids are fine.</i>

493
00:22:19.363 --> 00:22:21.616
<i>Okay? They're doing great.</i>

494
00:22:21.700 --> 00:22:22.997
<i>But if you rather want to stay there</i>

495
00:22:23.081 --> 00:22:24.124
<i>and help your ex-husband</i>

496
00:22:24.208 --> 00:22:25.660
<i>deal with the fact that
he's just made a fool</i>

497
00:22:25.744 --> 00:22:27.478
<i>of your whole family.
that's your choice.</i>

498
00:22:27.562 --> 00:22:29.080
<i>The helicopter will be
there in 20 minutes.</i>

499
00:22:29.164 --> 00:22:30.624
<i>I suggest you get on it.</i>

500
00:22:30.708 --> 00:22:33.168
[phone beeps]

501
00:22:33.865 --> 00:22:35.004
You should go.

502
00:22:39.276 --> 00:22:40.694
What about you?

503
00:22:40.779 --> 00:22:43.415
I'll be okay. I'm gonna
keep trying Whitney.

504
00:22:43.499 --> 00:22:45.430
Maybe I'll just go to
the airport and wait.

505
00:22:45.514 --> 00:22:47.173
I've got her flight number somewhere.

506
00:22:48.164 --> 00:22:50.875
I think I should talk to her
in person when she lands.

507
00:22:53.612 --> 00:22:55.474
She probably has a lot of questions.

508
00:22:59.776 --> 00:23:01.106
Thank you.

509
00:23:01.190 --> 00:23:02.764
For what?

510
00:23:03.411 --> 00:23:05.492
For this morning. today.

511
00:23:06.058 --> 00:23:07.590
All I did was yell at you.

512
00:23:08.037 --> 00:23:09.830
[quiet. gentle music]

513
00:23:09.914 --> 00:23:12.708
<i>♪♪♪</i>

514
00:23:14.084 --> 00:23:15.753
You're such a great mother. Helen.

515
00:23:20.257 --> 00:23:22.192
We've got four great kids. and...

516
00:23:23.052 --> 00:23:25.054
I know it's not because of me.

517
00:23:27.271 --> 00:23:28.922
I'm very grateful.

518
00:23:33.228 --> 00:23:35.356
[helicopter whirring]

519
00:23:36.523 --> 00:23:38.483
[somber music]

520
00:23:38.567 --> 00:23:39.652
<i>♪♪♪</i>

521
00:23:54.583 --> 00:23:55.709
<i>♪♪♪</i>

522
00:24:09.515 --> 00:24:10.849
[door closes]

523
00:24:10.933 --> 00:24:13.101
[newswoman] <i>There are several
major fires blanketing</i>

524
00:24:13.185 --> 00:24:15.408
<i>the stretch between Westwood
and Ventura County.</i>

525
00:24:15.492 --> 00:24:17.355
<i>Helicopters are still trying to get</i>

526
00:24:17.439 --> 00:24:20.692
<i>these wildfires under control
and they continue to drop</i>

527
00:24:20.776 --> 00:24:24.446
<i>gallons of water and retardant
onto the fires. Uh...</i>

528
00:24:24.530 --> 00:24:26.656
Hey. guys. You okay?

529
00:24:26.740 --> 00:24:28.408
We're fine.

530
00:24:28.492 --> 00:24:30.688
Trevor. let me see.
What happened? Trevor.

531
00:24:30.772 --> 00:24:34.039
Apparently. Brooklyn said
some shit about Dad.

532
00:24:34.123 --> 00:24:36.041
Trevor hit him. and he hit Trevor back.

533
00:24:37.126 --> 00:24:38.661
Honey. I'm so sorry.

534
00:24:38.745 --> 00:24:41.032
Yeah. well. it's not your fault
Dad fucks everything up.

535
00:24:41.116 --> 00:24:42.923
[Sasha] Who's hungry?

536
00:24:43.007 --> 00:24:44.758
Hey. Helen. you made it.

537
00:24:44.842 --> 00:24:46.051
- Hey.
- Great.

538
00:24:46.135 --> 00:24:49.220
- Trevor. can you take this?
- Yeah.

539
00:24:49.304 --> 00:24:51.223
- Talk to you for a second?
- Sure.

540
00:24:53.267 --> 00:24:54.726
[sighs]

541
00:24:54.810 --> 00:24:57.378
Listen... I'm really sorry

542
00:24:57.462 --> 00:25:00.299
that I just went and got
your kids like that.

543
00:25:01.205 --> 00:25:03.652
But the truth is that Trevor
called me and told me

544
00:25:03.736 --> 00:25:05.300
that Noah was at your house

545
00:25:05.384 --> 00:25:07.126
and that he didn't want to see him.

546
00:25:07.857 --> 00:25:10.310
So he asked me to come
and get him and Stacey.

547
00:25:11.673 --> 00:25:12.715
Really?

548
00:25:12.800 --> 00:25:15.538
Yeah. And I didn't want to
tell you over the phone.

549
00:25:16.714 --> 00:25:18.750
And I'm also sorry about last night.

550
00:25:19.378 --> 00:25:21.587
I-I-I was exhausted. and...

551
00:25:23.797 --> 00:25:26.902
Listen. I... I love you.

552
00:25:26.987 --> 00:25:29.192
But sometimes it frightens
me how big your world is.

553
00:25:29.276 --> 00:25:32.222
And it's not you who
should change; it's me.

554
00:25:32.306 --> 00:25:35.433
And-and... and that is
why I-I-I did what I did

555
00:25:35.517 --> 00:25:37.935
and went and got your kids.
'cause that is exactly

556
00:25:38.019 --> 00:25:39.493
the sort of thing that
you would have done.

557
00:25:44.359 --> 00:25:45.943
Well. I'm sorry. too.

558
00:25:48.030 --> 00:25:49.656
[whispers] Yeah. okay.

559
00:25:51.461 --> 00:25:53.618
- Glass of wine?
- Yeah. please.

560
00:25:53.702 --> 00:25:55.453
All right.

561
00:25:56.371 --> 00:25:58.333
[newsman] <i>Audrey Nelson
is one of the women</i>

562
00:25:58.417 --> 00:25:59.546
<i>accusing Solloway.</i>

563
00:25:59.630 --> 00:26:00.834
<i>We caught up with her this morning</i>

564
00:26:00.918 --> 00:26:02.794
<i>at the annual Women in Media Breakfast.</i>

565
00:26:03.748 --> 00:26:06.421
<i>Yes. I was in his
creative writing seminar</i>

566
00:26:06.505 --> 00:26:08.418
<i>my sophomore year at Livingston.</i>

567
00:26:08.502 --> 00:26:09.898
[newswoman] <i>Do you have a comment</i>

568
00:26:09.982 --> 00:26:12.137
<i>about the very damning article
that came out this morning</i>

569
00:26:12.221 --> 00:26:13.913
<i>concerning his behavior toward women?</i>

570
00:26:13.997 --> 00:26:15.890
[Audrey] <i>All I will say is that</i>

571
00:26:15.974 --> 00:26:17.350
<i>it's always terrifying</i>

572
00:26:17.434 --> 00:26:19.071
<i>to speak out against powerful men.</i>

573
00:26:19.155 --> 00:26:21.977
<i>especially if you have
been traumatized yourself.</i>

574
00:26:22.061 --> 00:26:23.732
<i>But I have been</i>

575
00:26:23.816 --> 00:26:26.311
<i>very encouraged by the sisterhood</i>

576
00:26:26.395 --> 00:26:28.236
<i>I've experienced here
today and on Twitter.</i>

577
00:26:28.320 --> 00:26:30.655
<i>and I just think it's-it's so important</i>

578
00:26:30.739 --> 00:26:34.159
<i>that we continue to support
and believe each other.</i>

579
00:26:34.243 --> 00:26:36.161
<i>because clearly there are men out there</i>

580
00:26:36.245 --> 00:26:38.246
<i>- who just truly hate women.</i>
- Okay.

581
00:26:38.330 --> 00:26:39.706
You guys. that's enough.
That's enough of this.

582
00:26:39.790 --> 00:26:41.416
Give me that. please.
Just give it to me.

583
00:26:41.500 --> 00:26:43.495
[Stacey] That woman's a publicity whore.

584
00:26:43.586 --> 00:26:44.861
She's gonna be on <i>The Talk</i> tomorrow.

585
00:26:44.945 --> 00:26:46.205
She's just trying to sell books.

586
00:26:46.289 --> 00:26:48.423
Yeah. sure. Stacey.
she's making it all up.

587
00:26:48.507 --> 00:26:49.966
That's what these men say.

588
00:26:50.050 --> 00:26:51.440
They say Dad's the real victim here.

589
00:26:51.524 --> 00:26:53.803
Oh. Stacey. please. no.

590
00:26:53.887 --> 00:26:55.579
But she's lying. Mom. isn't she?

591
00:26:55.663 --> 00:26:57.071
- [ringtone playing]
- Dad doesn't hate women.

592
00:26:57.155 --> 00:26:58.683
Hold on. This might be Whitney.

593
00:26:58.767 --> 00:27:00.295
Hello?

594
00:27:02.813 --> 00:27:04.248
How did you get this number?

595
00:27:05.732 --> 00:27:07.226
No. no comment.

596
00:27:07.310 --> 00:27:09.152
I'll be right back.

597
00:27:09.236 --> 00:27:11.363
Stacey. get off that site.

598
00:27:12.030 --> 00:27:14.324
[quiet. tense music]

599
00:27:14.408 --> 00:27:16.701
[Sasha] No. No. no. no. I-I hear you.

600
00:27:16.785 --> 00:27:19.079
Yeah. Listen. you're doing a great job.

601
00:27:20.289 --> 00:27:22.040
Well. the title's a great start.

602
00:27:22.124 --> 00:27:23.666
Now we just have to bring it home

603
00:27:23.750 --> 00:27:26.527
and-and get the tosspot's
name off it entirely.

604
00:27:26.611 --> 00:27:28.380
[sighs]

605
00:27:30.332 --> 00:27:32.426
Um. I-I'm gonna call you back.

606
00:27:35.172 --> 00:27:36.515
My mum says hi.

607
00:27:36.606 --> 00:27:38.056
Do you think this is funny?

608
00:27:38.140 --> 00:27:40.416
[sighs] Hey. I'm-I'm sorry
you had to hear that.

609
00:27:40.500 --> 00:27:43.037
I'm... I'm sure that sounded coarse.

610
00:27:43.121 --> 00:27:44.646
but I've been on the phone all day

611
00:27:44.730 --> 00:27:46.921
trying to navigate
what these accusations

612
00:27:47.005 --> 00:27:48.191
against Noah mean for my movie.

613
00:27:48.275 --> 00:27:51.236
He's really put us all
in a terrible situation.

614
00:27:51.320 --> 00:27:53.048
I just got a call from
the <i>New York Post.</i>

615
00:27:53.132 --> 00:27:54.697
- They wanted a quote.
- Mm-hmm. What'd you say?

616
00:27:54.781 --> 00:27:56.408
I said. "No comment."

617
00:27:57.326 --> 00:27:59.244
Okay.

618
00:27:59.328 --> 00:28:00.662
I mean. how did they get my number?

619
00:28:00.746 --> 00:28:02.330
[scoffs] Welcome to my world.

620
00:28:02.414 --> 00:28:04.457
Just wait till they start
stalking you at home.

621
00:28:04.541 --> 00:28:06.918
Listen. I've found that
if you don't respond.

622
00:28:07.002 --> 00:28:10.046
it just gets worse. so put
out a short statement

623
00:28:10.130 --> 00:28:12.483
asking for privacy for
you and your kids.

624
00:28:12.568 --> 00:28:13.429
[sighs]

625
00:28:13.514 --> 00:28:15.483
The best thing you can do right now

626
00:28:15.567 --> 00:28:17.176
is to distance them from their father.

627
00:28:17.260 --> 00:28:18.677
I can't do that.

628
00:28:19.650 --> 00:28:20.932
It would break Noah's heart.

629
00:28:21.016 --> 00:28:22.472
[scoffs] Sure. yeah.

630
00:28:22.556 --> 00:28:25.416
And what's really important
here is to protect

631
00:28:25.500 --> 00:28:28.440
Noah's feelings at all costs. right?

632
00:28:29.483 --> 00:28:31.415
You said you were making me a drink?

633
00:28:31.499 --> 00:28:33.069
[Stacey] Mom.

634
00:28:33.153 --> 00:28:35.196
What's up. Stace? You okay?

635
00:28:35.280 --> 00:28:37.031
Listen.

636
00:28:37.115 --> 00:28:38.867
[shakily] "I met Noah Solloway

637
00:28:38.951 --> 00:28:40.497
on the set of <i>Descent.</i>

638
00:28:40.581 --> 00:28:42.662
where I'm the script supervisor.

639
00:28:42.746 --> 00:28:44.414
He seemed like a gentleman.

640
00:28:44.498 --> 00:28:46.708
one of the few I've
met in this business.

641
00:28:46.792 --> 00:28:48.668
Or so I thought.

642
00:28:48.752 --> 00:28:52.002
Until a party one night
where he kissed me.

643
00:28:52.086 --> 00:28:53.722
then took off my clothes.

644
00:28:53.806 --> 00:28:55.800
ran away with them and left me there.

645
00:28:55.884 --> 00:28:58.136
- naked and terrified."
- Stacey.

646
00:28:58.220 --> 00:28:59.691
- Give me that.
- No!

647
00:28:59.775 --> 00:29:01.290
[crying] "I was outside in the dark

648
00:29:01.374 --> 00:29:03.353
at a Halloween party for children.

649
00:29:03.437 --> 00:29:05.476
I couldn't go anywhere.

650
00:29:05.560 --> 00:29:06.853
It was freezing.

651
00:29:06.937 --> 00:29:10.652
A cater waiter finally
came to my rescue.

652
00:29:10.736 --> 00:29:13.818
Noah Solloway gets off
on humiliating women."

653
00:29:13.902 --> 00:29:14.845
[sobs softly]

654
00:29:14.929 --> 00:29:16.404
Can I take that. please?

655
00:29:16.488 --> 00:29:19.741
[slow. somber music]

656
00:29:19.825 --> 00:29:22.419
I took him to that party.

657
00:29:23.445 --> 00:29:24.829
Is it true?

658
00:29:24.913 --> 00:29:26.956
Is it my fault?

659
00:29:27.040 --> 00:29:29.543
No. it's not your fault. Stacey.

660
00:29:31.461 --> 00:29:32.682
[sighs]

661
00:29:45.684 --> 00:29:47.018
Um...

662
00:29:47.102 --> 00:29:50.240
um. I'll make a... statement.

663
00:29:52.674 --> 00:29:53.979
Can you write it?

664
00:29:54.685 --> 00:29:55.698
Sure.

665
00:29:56.663 --> 00:29:58.390
What do you want it to say?

666
00:30:02.951 --> 00:30:05.816
"My family and I are
saddened and in shock

667
00:30:05.900 --> 00:30:09.040
after the revelations in
today's <i>Vanity Fair</i> article.

668
00:30:10.279 --> 00:30:12.965
I empathize greatly with the
women who came forward.

669
00:30:13.049 --> 00:30:14.671
and I admire them.

670
00:30:14.755 --> 00:30:16.765
All I can say about Noah Solloway

671
00:30:16.849 --> 00:30:20.218
is that he's been a good
father to our four children

672
00:30:20.302 --> 00:30:22.200
and they love him.

673
00:30:22.284 --> 00:30:24.555
I ask that people think
of these children.

674
00:30:24.639 --> 00:30:26.683
respect our privacy

675
00:30:26.767 --> 00:30:30.116
and not hold them responsible
for their father's actions."

676
00:30:31.936 --> 00:30:33.064
Thank you.

677
00:30:33.148 --> 00:30:34.406
[phone clicks]

678
00:30:34.490 --> 00:30:36.359
[seagulls calling]

679
00:30:39.790 --> 00:30:41.614
- Sasha?
- [Sasha] Yeah?

680
00:30:42.080 --> 00:30:43.783
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

681
00:30:43.867 --> 00:30:45.570
Um. she said she's gonna
put it out right away.

682
00:30:45.654 --> 00:30:47.328
What does that mean? Put it out where?

683
00:30:47.412 --> 00:30:49.727
Um. she's probably gonna get
in touch with Petra Ranes.

684
00:30:51.800 --> 00:30:54.156
- Your publicist knows Petra?
- Yeah.

685
00:30:54.240 --> 00:30:56.379
Sure. I mean. she was the one
that contacted everybody

686
00:30:56.463 --> 00:30:57.981
about the original article.

687
00:30:59.674 --> 00:31:01.259
So. now that it's all taken care of.

688
00:31:01.343 --> 00:31:03.052
uh. should we put our phones away

689
00:31:03.136 --> 00:31:04.552
and just try and relax a bit?

690
00:31:08.546 --> 00:31:10.528
[faint. echoing] Please.

691
00:31:10.612 --> 00:31:12.770
[slow. somber music]

692
00:31:12.854 --> 00:31:15.106
<i>♪♪♪</i>

693
00:31:15.190 --> 00:31:17.481
Do you want some wine?

694
00:31:19.538 --> 00:31:20.706
Yeah.

695
00:31:29.009 --> 00:31:31.039
<i>- ♪♪♪</i>
- [dialogue inaudible]

696
00:31:52.310 --> 00:31:56.147
[sniffs]

697
00:31:56.231 --> 00:31:57.107
[sighs]

698
00:32:05.907 --> 00:32:07.492
- Ooh.
- [Sasha] Oh... oh...

699
00:32:07.576 --> 00:32:08.910
- [chuckles] Sorry.
- It's just me.

700
00:32:08.994 --> 00:32:10.244
[chuckles]

701
00:32:10.328 --> 00:32:12.413
Whoa. Helen. your shoulders
are like bricks.

702
00:32:12.497 --> 00:32:14.382
Yeah.

703
00:32:15.529 --> 00:32:17.167
I guess I am pretty tense.

704
00:32:17.252 --> 00:32:18.961
Hey. it's gonna be fine.

705
00:32:19.861 --> 00:32:21.839
I've had my fair share of scandals.

706
00:32:21.923 --> 00:32:24.510
and in my experience. if
they're handled correctly.

707
00:32:24.594 --> 00:32:26.594
they'll blow over and...

708
00:32:27.591 --> 00:32:29.389
no one remembers.

709
00:32:31.303 --> 00:32:32.934
Thank you for helping me deal with this.

710
00:32:33.018 --> 00:32:34.146
Yeah. Sure.

711
00:32:34.230 --> 00:32:36.346
Can I run you a bubble bath?

712
00:32:36.430 --> 00:32:37.730
[chuckles]

713
00:32:37.814 --> 00:32:40.025
- Bubble bath?
- Yeah.

714
00:32:42.485 --> 00:32:44.070
Actually. that sounds very nice. yeah.

715
00:32:44.154 --> 00:32:45.363
- Thank you.
- Come on.

716
00:32:45.447 --> 00:32:48.491
[woman on TV] <i>...and I have
known each other forever.</i>

717
00:32:48.575 --> 00:32:49.957
<i>Our husbands grew up together...</i>

718
00:32:50.041 --> 00:32:51.619
[Helen] Hey. What happened to the movie?

719
00:32:51.703 --> 00:32:53.454
<i>- I was a bridesmaid in her wedding.</i>
- [laughs]

720
00:32:53.538 --> 00:32:56.244
<i>- She wore pants. It was iconic...
- Yes.</i>

721
00:32:56.328 --> 00:32:57.834
- Oh. great.
<i>- Um...</i>

722
00:32:57.918 --> 00:33:00.744
<i>But. unfortunately. that's
not... not what we're</i>

723
00:33:00.829 --> 00:33:02.596
<i>- going to talk about today.</i>
- [Sasha] Um. what's this?

724
00:33:02.680 --> 00:33:04.584
That's Eden Ellery.

725
00:33:05.133 --> 00:33:07.376
Remember you met her
at Carolina's party?

726
00:33:07.460 --> 00:33:09.500
Oh. yeah. Yeah.

727
00:33:09.584 --> 00:33:11.607
[Busy Philipps] <i>But Eden
is going through something</i>

728
00:33:11.691 --> 00:33:13.577
<i>very public. uh. right now.</i>

729
00:33:13.661 --> 00:33:14.917
<i>Something you might have heard about.</i>

730
00:33:15.001 --> 00:33:16.793
<i>Something that maybe even some of you</i>

731
00:33:16.877 --> 00:33:18.373
<i>have been through yourselves.</i>

732
00:33:18.457 --> 00:33:20.797
<i>and I really. really
wanted to talk about it.</i>

733
00:33:20.881 --> 00:33:22.150
<i>It was important.</i>

734
00:33:22.234 --> 00:33:24.318
<i>Uh. in case you guys have
been off Twitter all day.</i>

735
00:33:24.402 --> 00:33:26.404
<i>and if you have been. someone
explain to me how you do that.</i>

736
00:33:26.488 --> 00:33:27.905
- [chuckles]
<i>- Um...</i>

737
00:33:27.989 --> 00:33:30.032
- [audience laughs]
<i>- Eden was actually</i>

738
00:33:30.116 --> 00:33:33.244
<i>one of a handful of
women that came forward</i>

739
00:33:33.328 --> 00:33:36.372
<i>in</i> Vanity Fair <i>today. um. to talk about</i>

740
00:33:36.456 --> 00:33:38.124
<i>some pretty traumatic experiences</i>

741
00:33:38.208 --> 00:33:41.210
<i>of sexual harassment by Noah Solloway.</i>

742
00:33:41.294 --> 00:33:43.103
<i>You guys remember</i> Descent?

743
00:33:43.187 --> 00:33:44.505
<i>That book that was. like.</i>

744
00:33:44.589 --> 00:33:46.849
<i>a huge hit. like. five years ago?</i>

745
00:33:46.933 --> 00:33:49.328
- [Eden] <i>Ten.</i>
<i>- And you were his publicist?</i>

746
