00:45:55.403 --> 00:45:57.247
He is. isn't he?

984
00:45:57.331 --> 00:45:59.531
Mm-hmm.

985
00:46:00.238 --> 00:46:02.487
I keep thinking about my siblings.

986
00:46:02.571 --> 00:46:04.100
- The younger ones.
- Ugh.

987
00:46:04.184 --> 00:46:05.748
You remember Trevor and Stacey?

988
00:46:05.832 --> 00:46:07.831
- Oh. absolutely.
- Well. they're still in school.

989
00:46:07.915 --> 00:46:09.082
And... [scoffs]

990
00:46:09.166 --> 00:46:10.918
Stacey's 12.

991
00:46:11.002 --> 00:46:13.337
And now. any time anybody Googles them.

992
00:46:13.421 --> 00:46:14.776
for the rest of their lives...

993
00:46:14.861 --> 00:46:16.405
Or you.

994
00:46:18.259 --> 00:46:20.278
Look. I promise you.

995
00:46:21.512 --> 00:46:23.972
it's all gonna be okay.

996
00:46:24.599 --> 00:46:25.933
And. hey.

997
00:46:26.434 --> 00:46:29.978
you're still a bright.
beautiful young woman

998
00:46:30.062 --> 00:46:32.463
with a massive future.

999
00:46:33.311 --> 00:46:34.604
That hasn't changed.

1000
00:46:36.271 --> 00:46:38.231
How could he do this to us?

1001
00:46:38.316 --> 00:46:39.947
After everything he's
already put us through.

1002
00:46:40.031 --> 00:46:42.091
No. listen. listen.

1003
00:46:42.992 --> 00:46:45.410
Oh. God. this is gonna sound harsh.

1004
00:46:45.494 --> 00:46:48.497
but what's happening with
your father is inevitable.

1005
00:46:49.094 --> 00:46:52.192
You know? I've never met a man
who's quite so self-destructive.

1006
00:46:52.276 --> 00:46:53.894
so un...

1007
00:46:55.546 --> 00:46:56.755
careful.

1008
00:46:56.839 --> 00:46:59.361
And you have been wonderful
with him. darling.

1009
00:46:59.445 --> 00:47:00.694
You really have.

1010
00:47:00.778 --> 00:47:03.282
You've been the most diligent.

1011
00:47:03.366 --> 00:47:06.056
devoted daughter. but
sometimes. with toxic people.

1012
00:47:06.140 --> 00:47:08.075
you have to...

1013
00:47:09.101 --> 00:47:10.560
make a clean break. you know?

1014
00:47:10.644 --> 00:47:12.688
You have to save yourself.

1015
00:47:16.182 --> 00:47:18.735
I just spent a week with him in Montauk.

1016
00:47:18.819 --> 00:47:20.613
and he was amazing.

1017
00:47:21.863 --> 00:47:24.156
And I-I thought that he'd
turned a corner or something.

1018
00:47:24.241 --> 00:47:26.080
I-I thought that we would finally

1019
00:47:26.164 --> 00:47:27.666
be able to have a relationship.

1020
00:47:27.750 --> 00:47:29.621
What the hell were you doing
in Montauk in December?

1021
00:47:29.705 --> 00:47:31.282
You must have been fucking freezing.

1022
00:47:37.142 --> 00:47:39.842
Um. we were planning my wedding.

1023
00:47:40.445 --> 00:47:42.197
To who?

1024
00:47:44.177 --> 00:47:45.691
Uh. Colin.

1025
00:47:46.180 --> 00:47:47.538
He's my boyfriend.

1026
00:47:48.451 --> 00:47:50.393
Mazel tov!

1027
00:47:51.626 --> 00:47:54.354
Darling. that's fantastic.

1028
00:47:55.313 --> 00:47:57.149
Congratulations.

1029
00:47:57.233 --> 00:47:58.699
- Thanks.
- Oh!

1030
00:47:58.783 --> 00:48:00.652
Wow. Um...

1031
00:48:01.284 --> 00:48:03.413
Yeah. he's an... he's an
artist. too. actually.

1032
00:48:03.497 --> 00:48:04.698
No. You're kidding.

1033
00:48:04.782 --> 00:48:06.647
Well. wh-what sort?

1034
00:48:06.731 --> 00:48:09.119
Hang on. Do I know him?

1035
00:48:09.203 --> 00:48:11.591
Um. I don't think so. He's a painter.

1036
00:48:11.675 --> 00:48:13.152
- We met in art school.
- Well. then. why didn't you

1037
00:48:13.236 --> 00:48:15.792
bring him to the thing at
The Broad the other night?

1038
00:48:15.876 --> 00:48:17.544
I would have loved to
have met your fiancé.

1039
00:48:17.628 --> 00:48:20.410
That would have been a little
awkward. don't you think?

1040
00:48:20.494 --> 00:48:21.715
For you. maybe.

1041
00:48:23.384 --> 00:48:24.760
Is he any good?

1042
00:48:26.220 --> 00:48:28.055
Well. I. um...

1043
00:48:30.663 --> 00:48:32.432
He's very private about his work.

1044
00:48:32.517 --> 00:48:34.927
Ah. so he's tortured.

1045
00:48:35.011 --> 00:48:39.483
Oh. that's... that is so romantic.

1046
00:48:39.567 --> 00:48:41.569
- [glass clinks]
- [liquid pouring]

1047
00:48:45.353 --> 00:48:46.661
Young love.

1048
00:48:46.746 --> 00:48:49.326
We're actually just getting
married for a green card.

1049
00:48:49.410 --> 00:48:50.744
- Where's he from?
- [door opens]

1050
00:48:50.828 --> 00:48:53.747
- Ireland. He's Irish.
- [door closes]

1051
00:48:59.170 --> 00:49:00.702
Oh. You're still here?

1052
00:49:00.786 --> 00:49:03.465
[Layla] Oh. um. I'm sorry.

1053
00:49:03.549 --> 00:49:07.052
I didn't know if we were
finished working today

1054
00:49:07.136 --> 00:49:09.471
or if you were coming back.

1055
00:49:09.555 --> 00:49:11.227
So I thought I would wait.

1056
00:49:11.311 --> 00:49:13.183
No. I think I've got what I needed.

1057
00:49:13.267 --> 00:49:14.935
You can let yourself out.

1058
00:49:17.605 --> 00:49:19.523
[tense. atmospheric music]

1059
00:49:19.607 --> 00:49:22.276
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1060
00:49:25.988 --> 00:49:28.365
[door opens. closes]

1061
