How come you never asked me to model?

1062
00:49:35.331 --> 00:49:37.019
Huh? Oh. God. no.

1063
00:49:37.103 --> 00:49:38.667
You're too good for that.

1064
00:49:39.122 --> 00:49:41.128
You say that. but what does that mean?

1065
00:49:41.212 --> 00:49:43.853
Well. most of these girls
aren't very smart.

1066
00:49:43.937 --> 00:49:46.066
so modeling is a good gig for them.

1067
00:49:46.150 --> 00:49:47.574
But I want something more for you.

1068
00:49:47.658 --> 00:49:50.387
- More than...
- More than a body

1069
00:49:50.471 --> 00:49:52.739
that I manipulate for my art.

1070
00:49:59.097 --> 00:50:00.636
What about the other night. then?

1071
00:50:01.872 --> 00:50:03.206
[door opens]

1072
00:50:03.291 --> 00:50:05.460
- At the Chateau. when we...
- [door closes]

1073
00:50:10.842 --> 00:50:13.261
- When we what. Whitney?
- [elevator clanking]

1074
00:50:15.155 --> 00:50:19.326
Wasn't I just a body that you
could manipulate for your art?

1075
00:50:21.919 --> 00:50:23.770
You're-you're talking about
the night we made love.

1076
00:50:23.854 --> 00:50:25.630
[laughs]

1077
00:50:26.895 --> 00:50:28.925
Uh. we didn't make love.

1078
00:50:29.009 --> 00:50:31.998
You fucked me in front of your
rich friend to get him off.

1079
00:50:32.082 --> 00:50:33.202
Is that what you think happened?

1080
00:50:33.286 --> 00:50:37.423
It's not what I <i>think</i> happened.
I know that that happened.

1081
00:50:37.507 --> 00:50:40.631
- You whored me out.
- Okay. that's enough!

1082
00:50:43.817 --> 00:50:44.930
That's enough.

1083
00:50:46.819 --> 00:50:48.695
Now. um...

1084
00:50:48.779 --> 00:50:50.715
Listen to me. [exhales]

1085
00:50:51.515 --> 00:50:55.138
I know you're upset about what's
happening with your father.

1086
00:50:55.242 --> 00:50:57.496
You're angry and confused and
looking for someone to blame.

1087
00:50:57.580 --> 00:51:00.426
but. darling. don't
conflate those feelings

1088
00:51:00.510 --> 00:51:01.949
with what happened at the Chateau.

1089
00:51:02.033 --> 00:51:04.869
because that was absolutely
what you wanted.

1090
00:51:04.953 --> 00:51:06.456
That's not true.

1091
00:51:07.466 --> 00:51:08.799
That is not what I wanted.

1092
00:51:11.885 --> 00:51:14.554
Um. so why didn't you go. then?

1093
00:51:14.638 --> 00:51:17.245
Huh? For fuck's sake.

1094
00:51:17.329 --> 00:51:20.908
why didn't you bring your
fiancé to my opening?

1095
00:51:20.993 --> 00:51:22.381
I gave you a plus-one.

1096
00:51:23.272 --> 00:51:24.648
Andrea wanted to come.

1097
00:51:24.732 --> 00:51:26.233
Did you. um...

1098
00:51:26.317 --> 00:51:28.586
did you tell your fiancé
what happened between us?

1099
00:51:34.240 --> 00:51:36.076
Do you know what? If
I were you. Whitney.

1100
00:51:36.160 --> 00:51:38.931
I'd think long and hard

1101
00:51:39.015 --> 00:51:41.498
before making accusations.

1102
00:51:41.582 --> 00:51:43.750
You need friends right now.

1103
00:51:43.834 --> 00:51:45.460
What you should be worried about

1104
00:51:45.544 --> 00:51:47.662
is what's happening with your father.

1105
00:51:47.746 --> 00:51:52.406
Very worried. because it could
have severe repercussions

1106
00:51:52.490 --> 00:51:53.843
for your own career.

1107
00:51:53.927 --> 00:51:55.629
Now. I've been sitting here all day

1108
00:51:55.713 --> 00:51:56.983
since the article came out.

1109
00:51:57.067 --> 00:51:58.782
trying to think how I could help you.

1110
00:51:59.999 --> 00:52:01.622
And here's the thing:

1111
00:52:01.707 --> 00:52:05.071
Dashiell is opening a
gallery on 21st Street.

1112
00:52:05.641 --> 00:52:10.026
and he is planning to have
me as his inaugural artist.

1113
00:52:10.110 --> 00:52:14.063
and we had discussed
the possibility of you

1114
00:52:14.147 --> 00:52:16.280
curating my first show.

1115
00:52:17.287 --> 00:52:20.857
But if that's how you really
feel about him and me.

1116
00:52:21.789 --> 00:52:24.891
then perhaps we ought
to revisit that idea.

1117
00:52:40.153 --> 00:52:42.284
Why did you hit me in Paris?

1118
00:52:42.726 --> 00:52:44.853
[tense music]

1119
00:52:44.937 --> 00:52:46.855
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1120
00:52:46.939 --> 00:52:48.232
Hit you?

1121
00:52:50.303 --> 00:52:51.387
I didn't.

1122
00:52:54.125 --> 00:52:55.365
You did.

1123
00:52:56.365 --> 00:52:57.434
I remember.

1124
00:52:57.518 --> 00:52:59.993
[chuckles] Oh. Christ.

1125
00:53:01.809 --> 00:53:04.779
Ah. Whitney. I can see that
our little tiff in Paris

1126
00:53:04.863 --> 00:53:06.501
has got blown out of all proportion

1127
00:53:06.585 --> 00:53:08.849
inside your gorgeous little head.

1128
00:53:08.933 --> 00:53:11.482
But. darling. for something so dramatic

1129
00:53:11.566 --> 00:53:14.114
to transpire. there would
have to be passion

1130
00:53:14.198 --> 00:53:15.675
in the relationship.
and sweet as you are.

1131
00:53:15.759 --> 00:53:18.178
I never had those kinds
of feelings for you.

1132
00:53:26.437 --> 00:53:28.855
You should. um... you
should probably go.

1133
00:53:28.939 --> 00:53:31.066
You don't want to miss
your flight. right?

1134
00:53:36.697 --> 00:53:38.157
Okay. um...

1135
00:53:42.123 --> 00:53:43.787
Could you at least take
me to the airport?

1136
00:53:43.871 --> 00:53:46.164
I just... I don't really want
to leave things like this.

1137
00:53:46.248 --> 00:53:48.166
You know. I don't think
that's a great idea.

1138
00:53:48.250 --> 00:53:52.671
Um. it was probably a
mistake to invite you over.

1139
00:53:54.915 --> 00:53:56.257
I'm in a good place right now.

1140
00:53:56.341 --> 00:53:57.868
You know. I'm very...

1141
00:53:58.719 --> 00:54:00.179
productive.

1142
00:54:01.725 --> 00:54:02.726
I don't...

1143
00:54:03.496 --> 00:54:06.623
I don't want to get
trammeled in the past.

1144
00:54:11.247 --> 00:54:13.374
[sets down glass]

1145
00:54:16.445 --> 00:54:18.446
[slow. somber music]

1146
00:54:18.530 --> 00:54:20.365
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1147
00:54:46.934 --> 00:54:49.061
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1148
00:55:08.803 --> 00:55:10.221
[sighs]

1149
00:55:10.306 --> 00:55:12.016
