1209
00:58:56.248 --> 00:58:58.719
My mom's second husband just
died of pancreatic cancer.

1210
00:58:58.803 --> 00:59:01.104
My mom's dad has Alzheimer's.
My mom hasn't worked

1211
00:59:01.188 --> 00:59:03.208
in ten years so that she could raise us.

1212
00:59:03.292 --> 00:59:06.109
So we were all kind of counting
on my dad's book to come out.

1213
00:59:06.193 --> 00:59:08.264
You know. so my siblings
could stay in school.

1214
00:59:11.156 --> 00:59:14.177
Um. that's a lot.

1215
00:59:14.261 --> 00:59:16.613
Yeah. And I bet you never even bothered

1216
00:59:16.697 --> 00:59:18.023
to check whether he had kids

1217
00:59:18.108 --> 00:59:19.902
before speaking out
against him. did you?

1218
00:59:23.543 --> 00:59:25.914
Actually. I knew he had children.

1219
00:59:25.998 --> 00:59:27.463
Did you ever stop to think

1220
00:59:27.547 --> 00:59:30.300
how this might affect other
people. besides my father?

1221
00:59:35.746 --> 00:59:36.973
Yes. Whitney.

1222
00:59:37.057 --> 00:59:39.192
I thought about it long and hard.

1223
00:59:39.276 --> 00:59:41.643
and I decided that it was worth it.

1224
00:59:41.728 --> 00:59:42.895
Wow.

1225
00:59:42.979 --> 00:59:45.523
Look. I worshipped your father.

1226
00:59:45.607 --> 00:59:48.526
Okay? All I ever wanted
was to be a writer.

1227
00:59:48.610 --> 00:59:50.983
and I'd read <i>Descent.</i>
like. a dozen times.

1228
00:59:51.067 --> 00:59:54.657
so getting to study with
Noah Solloway was a dream.

1229
00:59:54.741 --> 00:59:56.953
So you're mad at my father
because he didn't live up

1230
00:59:57.037 --> 00:59:58.563
to your fantasies of him?

1231
00:59:58.647 --> 01:00:00.329
No. that's not it.

1232
01:00:00.413 --> 01:00:03.040
So. what is it. Audrey?
He didn't like your work?

1233
01:00:03.124 --> 01:00:05.501
He didn't even give my writing a chance.

1234
01:00:05.585 --> 01:00:07.422
He took one look at me
and decided he knew

1235
01:00:07.506 --> 01:00:10.464
how much I was worth before
he'd read a thing I'd written.

1236
01:00:10.549 --> 01:00:12.051
Why would he do that?

1237
01:00:13.426 --> 01:00:15.663
Because he didn't respect me. Whitney.

1238
01:00:15.747 --> 01:00:17.597
Well. maybe your writing
just wasn't very good.

1239
01:00:17.681 --> 01:00:19.223
Did you ever consider that?

1240
01:00:19.307 --> 01:00:21.268
[laughs]

1241
01:00:23.103 --> 01:00:24.729
Yeah. yeah. You're right.

1242
01:00:25.170 --> 01:00:27.399
At the time. it-it really wasn't.

1243
01:00:28.483 --> 01:00:30.933
I was very young when I
was in Noah's class.

1244
01:00:31.017 --> 01:00:34.124
and I was honestly desperate
for his guidance.

1245
01:00:34.208 --> 01:00:38.172
but he didn't evaluate my
work; he evaluated me.

1246
01:00:38.256 --> 01:00:40.264
He told me that I had no inner life.

1247
01:00:40.348 --> 01:00:41.830
Well. do you?

1248
01:00:43.809 --> 01:00:45.765
Everyone has an inner life.

1249
01:00:45.849 --> 01:00:50.509
What he meant was that I
didn't share his inner life

1250
01:00:50.593 --> 01:00:53.902
and that I wasn't trying
hard enough to hide that.

1251
01:00:53.986 --> 01:00:59.043
So. because I was writing about
being young and being female.

1252
01:00:59.127 --> 01:01:01.599
he assumed that I had
nothing interesting to say.

1253
01:01:02.846 --> 01:01:04.728
Have you ever experienced that?

1254
01:01:06.907 --> 01:01:08.940
I mean. look. it just sounds
like he was a shitty professor.

1255
01:01:09.024 --> 01:01:10.509
and I'm sorry that he
hurt your feelings.

1256
01:01:10.593 --> 01:01:13.304
but that's not a reason to
ruin his entire career.

1257
01:01:13.388 --> 01:01:14.946
- It's not?
- No.

1258
01:01:15.442 --> 01:01:16.914
Why not?

1259
01:01:18.757 --> 01:01:20.493
Why didn't you just drop the class?

1260
01:01:20.577 --> 01:01:25.213
I did. Well. actually. first.
I complained to my dean.

1261
01:01:25.297 --> 01:01:27.966
who told me that I needed
to grow a thicker skin.

1262
01:01:28.050 --> 01:01:29.335
So. then I dropped the class.

1263
01:01:29.419 --> 01:01:32.960
And it was a class that
I needed for my major.

1264
01:01:33.044 --> 01:01:34.860
so I dropped that. too.

1265
01:01:34.944 --> 01:01:38.730
And I stopped writing for three years.

1266
01:01:38.814 --> 01:01:41.520
and I went into a pretty
serious depression.

1267
01:01:41.604 --> 01:01:44.841
That's terrible. Audrey. but
that's not my father's fault.

1268
01:01:45.894 --> 01:01:47.820
So. whose fault is it?

1269
01:01:47.904 --> 01:01:49.940
I don't know.

1270
01:01:50.024 --> 01:01:51.274
I don't think it's anybody's fault.

1271
01:01:51.358 --> 01:01:53.068
I think it's just
something that happened.

1272
01:01:54.194 --> 01:01:56.279
Right. Okay. right.

1273
01:01:56.363 --> 01:01:59.282
That is exactly what I
thought. too. at the time.

1274
01:01:59.730 --> 01:02:04.328
But the truth is that the
way that Noah spoke to me.

1275
01:02:04.412 --> 01:02:06.216
the way that he treated me

1276
01:02:06.860 --> 01:02:11.627
confirmed my own worst
fears about myself.

1277
01:02:11.711 --> 01:02:14.922
Things that I had heard in one
way or another my entire life.

1278
01:02:15.006 --> 01:02:16.936
That I was worthless

1279
01:02:17.020 --> 01:02:21.150
and stupid and not hot enough.

1280
01:02:21.234 --> 01:02:23.990
just generally a waste of space.

1281
01:02:24.975 --> 01:02:27.894
And it really wasn't until I
started writing my memoir

1282
01:02:27.978 --> 01:02:30.730
that I even began to ask myself.

1283
01:02:30.814 --> 01:02:36.082
"Okay. why have I thought
this way all this time?

1284
01:02:36.166 --> 01:02:39.661
Why did I just assume
that the problem is me?

1285
01:02:39.745 --> 01:02:41.618
Why do I have to leave the class?

1286
01:02:41.702 --> 01:02:45.512
And why is the way that Noah
treated me considered normal?"

1287
01:02:47.020 --> 01:02:49.123
Think about it. Whitney. okay?

1288
01:02:49.207 --> 01:02:53.378
We give men like him
such unbelievable rope.

1289
01:02:54.921 --> 01:02:56.792
We will do anything...

1290
01:02:57.249 --> 01:02:59.342
Anything... to protect their egos

1291
01:02:59.426 --> 01:03:03.220
when they continuously and
carelessly destroy ours

1292
01:03:03.304 --> 01:03:04.639
without consequence.

1293
01:03:04.723 --> 01:03:07.240
I mean. why? Why does it
have to be like that?

1294
01:03:07.324 --> 01:03:08.643
I agree.

1295
01:03:08.727 --> 01:03:11.228
The world is a shitty
place. and it's not fair.

1296
01:03:11.312 --> 01:03:13.814
But I still feel like you're
using your private beef

1297
01:03:13.898 --> 01:03:15.952
with my father to promote
your book sales.

1298
01:03:16.036 --> 01:03:18.655
and that's just...
that's fucking bullshit.

1299
01:03:20.989 --> 01:03:22.407
Wow.

1300
01:03:24.292 --> 01:03:26.211
Someone really did a number on you.

1301
01:03:27.454 --> 01:03:29.372
Look. I've had tough experiences

1302
01:03:29.456 --> 01:03:32.004
with older men. too...
teachers. bosses...

1303
01:03:32.115 --> 01:03:34.378
But I'm adult enough to admit
that sometimes the problem

1304
01:03:34.462 --> 01:03:36.554
was just that I wanted to fuck
them and I shouldn't have.

1305
01:03:36.638 --> 01:03:38.245
Or I wanted them to fuck
me and they didn't.

1306
01:03:38.809 --> 01:03:40.255
Or maybe it's just that sometimes.

1307
01:03:40.339 --> 01:03:41.550
relationships between men and women

1308
01:03:41.634 --> 01:03:44.119
get weird and awkward.
and that's normal.

1309
01:03:44.203 --> 01:03:46.239
But that doesn't mean
all men should burn.

1310
01:03:46.323 --> 01:03:48.033
Mm-hmm. Okay.

1311
01:03:49.309 --> 01:03:52.186
I wanted to sleep with
your dad. You're right.

1312
01:03:52.614 --> 01:03:55.856
And. yeah. he didn't want
to sleep with me back.

1313
01:03:55.940 --> 01:03:58.397
and that hurt my feelings.

1314
01:03:58.481 --> 01:04:02.007
But. Whitney. when you want to
sleep with these older guys.

1315
01:04:02.091 --> 01:04:05.215
ask yourself. like. what are
you really attracted to?

1316
01:04:05.299 --> 01:04:08.411
Is it them. or is it their power

1317
01:04:08.495 --> 01:04:11.747
and their authority. their
agency in the world?

1318
01:04:11.831 --> 01:04:15.014
Like. how they can get
the kind of shit done

1319
01:04:15.098 --> 01:04:16.854
that you can only dream
of. and they do it

1320
01:04:16.938 --> 01:04:19.837
without even breaking a
sweat because the world

1321
01:04:19.921 --> 01:04:22.736
just offers itself up to
them on a silver platter.

1322
01:04:22.820 --> 01:04:25.762
Ask yourself. do you
really want to fuck them.

1323
01:04:25.846 --> 01:04:27.514
or do you want to be them?

1324
01:04:33.103 --> 01:04:35.422
Look. I'm sorry about your family.

1325
01:04:35.506 --> 01:04:37.045
I really am.

1326
01:04:37.625 --> 01:04:38.849
And. yeah.

1327
01:04:38.933 --> 01:04:41.819
I-I considered not speaking
up for this very reason.

1328
01:04:41.903 --> 01:04:43.380
'cause I thought... [sighs]

1329
01:04:44.094 --> 01:04:48.657
"God. what if my individual
trauma is not worth blowing up

1330
01:04:48.741 --> 01:04:50.890
anyone else's life in order to tell?"

1331
01:04:50.974 --> 01:04:52.747
But if we all do that.

1332
01:04:52.831 --> 01:04:56.017
if we all think like that.

1333
01:04:57.060 --> 01:04:59.795
then none of these stories
are ever gonna get told.

1334
01:04:59.879 --> 01:05:02.590
So. when does it become enough?

1335
01:05:03.758 --> 01:05:05.945
When does our need to tell our stories

1336
01:05:06.029 --> 01:05:08.304
become greater than their need

1337
01:05:08.388 --> 01:05:10.202
to preserve the status quo?

1338
01:05:10.286 --> 01:05:13.052
Is it when we're abused
or when we're raped?

1339
01:05:13.136 --> 01:05:14.332
Or is that even enough?

1340
01:05:14.416 --> 01:05:17.176
Because. honestly. it depends
on the man in question. right?

1341
01:05:18.565 --> 01:05:21.766
Really. what I'm saying is
that this is the problem.

1342
01:05:21.850 --> 01:05:26.322
We constantly debate whether we
even have the right to speak.

1343
01:05:26.406 --> 01:05:30.614
Like. we. we monitor what we
say and our choice of words.

1344
01:05:30.698 --> 01:05:33.184
And. oh. are we sitting.
or are we standing?

1345
01:05:33.268 --> 01:05:34.246
And. oh. we're... if we're sitting.

1346
01:05:34.330 --> 01:05:35.831
well. how are we sitting?

1347
01:05:35.915 --> 01:05:37.898
And if we're standing.
well. what are we wearing?

1348
01:05:37.982 --> 01:05:39.627
And are our voices pitched just right?

1349
01:05:39.711 --> 01:05:40.795
I mean. think about
the mental gymnastics

1350
01:05:40.879 --> 01:05:44.483
that you have to do in order
to just have a conversation.

1351
01:05:44.567 --> 01:05:46.217
And now imagine what it would be like

1352
01:05:46.301 --> 01:05:48.981
if we lived in a world where we
didn't have to do any of that.

1353
01:05:49.928 --> 01:05:51.445
Where we can just speak.

1354
01:05:53.179 --> 01:05:55.017
We're not the problem. Whitney.

1355
01:05:55.101 --> 01:05:56.310
They are.

1356
01:05:57.264 --> 01:06:00.022
All I want is just to live in a world

1357
01:06:00.106 --> 01:06:02.691
where we're not. like. weird
second-class citizens

1358
01:06:02.775 --> 01:06:05.444
whose first job is to
make men comfortable.

1359
01:06:05.528 --> 01:06:07.672
and then we'll be allowed to speak.

1360
01:06:08.549 --> 01:06:10.134
[sighs]

1361
01:06:12.452 --> 01:06:15.428
And. yeah. I think that your dad is

1362
01:06:15.512 --> 01:06:17.515
an impediment to that world.

1363
01:06:18.821 --> 01:06:21.269
And from what I read in that article.

1364
01:06:22.170 --> 01:06:24.005
I'm not the only one.

1365
01:06:25.070 --> 01:06:28.384
So... I felt that I needed

1366
01:06:28.468 --> 01:06:29.995
to say something. and I...

1367
01:06:31.345 --> 01:06:33.448
I just hope that you
can understand that.

1368
01:06:34.682 --> 01:06:36.600
[somber music]

1369
01:06:36.684 --> 01:06:38.811
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1370
01:06:47.549 --> 01:06:48.801
She lives.

1371
01:06:48.886 --> 01:06:51.763
I told you my flight was canceled.

1372
01:06:52.975 --> 01:06:55.269
Yeah. and then you went radio silent.

1373
01:06:56.953 --> 01:06:59.083
I've been worried about you. Whit.

1374
01:06:59.167 --> 01:07:02.404
I'm sorry. I'm so tired.
I had the craziest day.

1375
01:07:02.488 --> 01:07:04.212
I just need to go to bed.

1376
01:07:05.665 --> 01:07:07.667
- Wait a bit.
- Come on. Colin.

1377
01:07:09.467 --> 01:07:10.843
[sighs]

1378
01:07:12.055 --> 01:07:13.764
What's going on with you?

1379
01:07:13.849 --> 01:07:16.560
We barely spoke the entire
time you were in Montauk.

1380
01:07:21.980 --> 01:07:24.023
[exhales sharply]

1381
01:07:25.191 --> 01:07:26.942
Nothing's going on with me. Colin.

1382
01:07:27.026 --> 01:07:28.819
except for the fact
that my father just got

1383
01:07:28.903 --> 01:07:30.654
Harvey Weinstein'd. and my whole future

1384
01:07:30.738 --> 01:07:32.991
just got flushed down the toilet.

1385
01:07:35.030 --> 01:07:37.370
And I don't really think I owe
you anything at the moment.

1386
01:07:37.454 --> 01:07:38.954
Not even a conversation.

1387
01:07:39.038 --> 01:07:41.207
- I'm going to bed.
- I'm sorry. but you can't.

1388
01:07:41.291 --> 01:07:43.477
I know you've had a long day.
and I'm sure you're very tired.

1389
01:07:43.561 --> 01:07:45.054
but we have to talk.

1390
01:07:45.196 --> 01:07:48.464
You can't just disappear.
ignore my calls and texts.

1391
01:07:48.548 --> 01:07:49.965
That's not okay.

1392
01:07:50.049 --> 01:07:52.359
I'm about to be your husband.
for Christ's sake.

1393
01:07:58.558 --> 01:07:59.867
I can't do this.

1394
01:08:01.807 --> 01:08:03.559
You can't do what? Can't talk to me?

1395
01:08:05.149 --> 01:08:06.568
I can't marry you.

1396
01:08:14.831 --> 01:08:16.164
Okay.

1397
01:08:18.214 --> 01:08:19.924
Why not?

1398
01:08:23.981 --> 01:08:25.960
'Cause I fucked someone else.

1399
01:08:36.220 --> 01:08:37.889
[exhales]

1400
01:08:46.445 --> 01:08:47.780
Who?

1401
01:08:49.466 --> 01:08:50.793
Furkat.

1402
01:08:51.652 --> 01:08:52.833
The photographer?

1403
01:08:53.400 --> 01:08:55.353
We used to date back in New York.

1404
01:08:56.270 --> 01:08:57.313
What?

1405
01:08:58.242 --> 01:08:59.493
It only happened once.

1406
01:08:59.578 --> 01:09:00.829
That night at The Broad.

1407
01:09:04.602 --> 01:09:06.270
Were you with him today?

1408
01:09:06.355 --> 01:09:08.279
Yes. but nothing happened.

1409
01:09:09.504 --> 01:09:10.880
You don't have to believe me.

1410
01:09:10.964 --> 01:09:12.298
but it's the truth.

1411
01:09:15.347 --> 01:09:17.099
I believe you.

1412
01:09:25.808 --> 01:09:27.188
Do you love him. then?

1413
01:09:28.882 --> 01:09:30.105
No.

1414
01:09:30.722 --> 01:09:32.077
He's an asshole.

1415
01:09:33.836 --> 01:09:35.634
But clearly. so am I.

1416
01:09:36.508 --> 01:09:38.407
You should leave me. Colin.

1417
01:09:38.491 --> 01:09:39.926
We should break up.

1418
01:09:42.962 --> 01:09:44.354
If that's what you want.

1419
01:09:45.461 --> 01:09:47.058
Why isn't it what you want?

1420
01:09:50.712 --> 01:09:53.398
I guess I'd like to know
what's going on first.

1421
01:09:54.908 --> 01:09:56.467
If we can fix things.

1422
01:09:56.951 --> 01:09:58.011
Right.

1423
01:09:58.761 --> 01:10:00.585
Right. because. if we don't fix things.

1424
01:10:00.669 --> 01:10:01.825
you get deported.

1425
01:10:02.589 --> 01:10:04.026
Jesus!

1426
01:10:04.839 --> 01:10:06.525
Fucking Christ. Whitney.

1427
01:10:06.609 --> 01:10:08.826
is that really what you
think this is about?

1428
01:10:09.426 --> 01:10:11.315
- A green card?
- Isn't it?

1429
01:10:11.399 --> 01:10:14.585
I hate this godforsaken country.

1430
01:10:15.274 --> 01:10:17.130
I'd love to go home.

1431
01:10:18.228 --> 01:10:20.240
I'm not with you because
I need a green card.

1432
01:10:20.324 --> 01:10:23.522
I need a green card because I
fucking want to be with you.

1433
01:10:29.107 --> 01:10:31.275
[Colin sighs heavily]

1434
01:10:31.360 --> 01:10:33.212
[quiet. atmospheric music]

1435
01:10:33.296 --> 01:10:34.380
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1436
01:10:52.774 --> 01:10:55.860
[sniffles. sighs]

1437
01:11:08.275 --> 01:11:09.652
I'm sorry.

1438
01:11:12.574 --> 01:11:15.452
I know I'm an impossibly slow painter.

1439
01:11:16.714 --> 01:11:18.757
I wish I could just turn out work

1440
01:11:18.841 --> 01:11:21.299
like some of my peers. like Furkat.

1441
01:11:21.383 --> 01:11:23.734
an-and sell them for millions of dollars

1442
01:11:23.818 --> 01:11:25.313
and buy us a house.

1443
01:11:26.093 --> 01:11:28.701
I will get there someday. I know I will.

1444
01:11:29.201 --> 01:11:31.854
But just don't fucking
give up on me yet.

1445
01:11:32.727 --> 01:11:34.523
I'm so... I'm so sorry.

1446
01:11:34.607 --> 01:11:37.819
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1447
01:11:41.739 --> 01:11:43.216
I love you so much.

1448
01:11:48.830 --> 01:11:50.957
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1449
01:11:58.972 --> 01:12:01.592
- [knocking on door]
- [Noah] Whitney. you in there?

1450
01:12:01.676 --> 01:12:03.427
Whitney?

1451
01:12:06.472 --> 01:12:07.630
Oh. thank God.

1452
01:12:07.714 --> 01:12:09.398
What's up?

1453
01:12:09.482 --> 01:12:11.265
I'm sorry. uh. just showing up.

1454
01:12:11.349 --> 01:12:13.104
We didn't know where you
were. We were worried.

1455
01:12:13.188 --> 01:12:14.897
Oh. okay. well. I'm
fine. so you can leave.

1456
01:12:14.981 --> 01:12:16.868
No. I need to talk. I need to talk.

1457
01:12:16.952 --> 01:12:18.606
You've seen the news. right?

1458
01:12:19.426 --> 01:12:20.486
Of course.

1459
01:12:20.570 --> 01:12:24.031
Uh. look. it's terrible.
but I need you to know

1460
01:12:24.115 --> 01:12:26.293
there is... that article.
the allegations.

1461
01:12:26.377 --> 01:12:28.799
what those women are saying.
there is no truth in it at all.

1462
01:12:30.165 --> 01:12:31.330
Can I come in?

1463
01:12:31.415 --> 01:12:32.761
Please?

1464
01:12:34.208 --> 01:12:36.419
Um...

1465
01:12:37.461 --> 01:12:38.921
[clicks tongue]

1466
01:12:40.673 --> 01:12:43.467
Uh. Whitney. the-the real story is-is...

1467
01:12:43.551 --> 01:12:45.886
it's just much. much more complicated.

1468
01:12:45.970 --> 01:12:47.137
Look. that doesn't matter.

1469
01:12:47.221 --> 01:12:49.556
The point is. I'm your
father and I love you

1470
01:12:49.640 --> 01:12:51.308
and you don't need to worry.

1471
01:12:51.392 --> 01:12:53.665
because your mom and I. we're
gonna take care of this.

1472
01:12:53.749 --> 01:12:56.339
- How?
- What do you mean?

1473
01:12:56.423 --> 01:12:57.980
How are you gonna take care of it?

1474
01:12:58.064 --> 01:12:59.487
Well. we're gonna fight it.

1475
01:12:59.571 --> 01:13:01.115
You really think that's
such a good idea?

1476
01:13:01.199 --> 01:13:02.215
Well. what choice have I got?

1477
01:13:02.299 --> 01:13:03.237
I... we're not gonna let these women

1478
01:13:03.321 --> 01:13:04.922
ruin our lives.

1479
01:13:05.990 --> 01:13:07.842
I'm so tired. I have to go to sleep.

1480
01:13:07.927 --> 01:13:09.284
- No. okay. No. of course.
- I don't want to talk about it.

1481
01:13:09.368 --> 01:13:10.994
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- Okay. Whitney. I understand.

1482
01:13:11.078 --> 01:13:12.886
- I just need you to know...
- Mr. Solloway. it's very late.

1483
01:13:14.507 --> 01:13:16.300
You should go.

1484
01:13:17.122 --> 01:13:18.498
Hi. Colin. Hi.

1485
01:13:18.582 --> 01:13:19.951
This is. uh. no disrespect.

1486
01:13:20.035 --> 01:13:21.368
This is just between me
and my daughter. okay?

1487
01:13:21.452 --> 01:13:22.965
She doesn't want to talk to you.

1488
01:13:23.049 --> 01:13:24.383
She just asked you to leave.

1489
01:13:26.260 --> 01:13:27.135
[loud knock on door]

1490
01:13:27.219 --> 01:13:28.582
- [sighs]
- Oh. my God.

1491
01:13:28.666 --> 01:13:31.165
Thank God. Whitney.

1492
01:13:32.016 --> 01:13:34.226
Oh. my God. we were
so worried about you.

1493
01:13:34.310 --> 01:13:35.978
[Whitney] Uh. okay.

1494
01:13:36.062 --> 01:13:38.146
- Well. I'm fine.
- Okay.

1495
01:13:38.230 --> 01:13:39.648
All right. listen. I need
to talk to everybody.

1496
01:13:39.732 --> 01:13:41.525
Okay? I just... I need
to... I just... I just...

1497
01:13:41.609 --> 01:13:43.718
I found something out. and
I need to tell all of you.

1498
01:13:43.802 --> 01:13:47.212
So. can we please just sit
down and talk? Please.

1499
01:13:51.659 --> 01:13:53.535
Okay. uh. uh...

1500
01:13:54.183 --> 01:13:56.454
all of this is my fault.

1501
01:13:56.539 --> 01:13:59.481
Everything that's happening
right now is my fault.

1502
01:14:00.419 --> 01:14:01.542
What?

1503
01:14:03.589 --> 01:14:06.561
Because Sasha wants writing credit

1504
01:14:06.645 --> 01:14:08.321
for your dad's movie.

1505
01:14:08.405 --> 01:14:10.818
And I... he...

1506
01:14:11.522 --> 01:14:14.183
he used something I said
that I should not have said.

1507
01:14:14.267 --> 01:14:15.637
and he gave it to a reporter.

1508
01:14:15.721 --> 01:14:17.473
and now she's using it
against your father.

1509
01:14:17.557 --> 01:14:20.087
But your dad didn't do anything wrong.

1510
01:14:20.171 --> 01:14:21.570
They're just spinning it.

1511
01:14:21.654 --> 01:14:23.025
Can you take Stacey and
Trevor for ice cream?

1512
01:14:23.109 --> 01:14:24.347
- Yeah.
- No. we're not children.

1513
01:14:24.431 --> 01:14:25.819
- I want to stay.
- No. please. I need you to go.

1514
01:14:25.903 --> 01:14:27.779
[Trevor] Sure. Yeah.

1515
01:14:27.863 --> 01:14:29.698
Ice cream sounds great.

1516
01:14:29.782 --> 01:14:31.409
Come on. Stace.

1517
01:14:32.284 --> 01:14:34.036
Hey. you sure you're okay?

1518
01:14:34.120 --> 01:14:35.813
- Yep.
- All right.

1519
01:14:35.897 --> 01:14:37.581
Let's go. guys.

1520
01:14:40.208 --> 01:14:42.919
Look. I'm not sure exactly
what I said. but I think

1521
01:14:43.004 --> 01:14:45.213
maybe it was that you and
Eden were sleeping together.

1522
01:14:45.297 --> 01:14:46.632
- Oh. Jesus. Helen.
- I'm sorry.

1523
01:14:46.716 --> 01:14:48.483
[Helen] I-I really can't imagine that he

1524
01:14:48.567 --> 01:14:50.069
would do something like
this. I'm really sorry.

1525
01:14:50.153 --> 01:14:52.161
Mom. why are you apologizing to him?

1526
01:14:52.596 --> 01:14:54.389
Because I fucked up.

1527
01:14:54.473 --> 01:14:56.127
How. exactly?

1528
01:14:56.211 --> 01:14:58.185
Uh. even if Sasha started it.

1529
01:14:58.269 --> 01:15:00.281
does that mean these women are lying?

1530
01:15:00.385 --> 01:15:01.734
Does that mean that Dad didn't do

1531
01:15:01.818 --> 01:15:03.565
the things he's being accused of?

1532
01:15:03.649 --> 01:15:06.080
You believe these women
over me? I'm your father.

1533
01:15:07.819 --> 01:15:09.988
Nobody's saying that they're lying.

1534
01:15:10.072 --> 01:15:12.088
I'm just saying that maybe
they're exaggerating

1535
01:15:12.172 --> 01:15:13.195
what happened to them.

1536
01:15:13.279 --> 01:15:15.661
- Why would they do that?
- For attention.

1537
01:15:15.745 --> 01:15:17.746
I mean. these things happen
on a spectrum. okay?

1538
01:15:17.830 --> 01:15:19.686
Like. what they're describing

1539
01:15:19.770 --> 01:15:22.599
is awkward. yes. and
uncomfortable. certainly.

1540
01:15:22.684 --> 01:15:23.950
It's not abuse.

1541
01:15:24.034 --> 01:15:25.295
And by calling it abuse.

1542
01:15:25.379 --> 01:15:27.708
you just turn women into victims.

1543
01:15:27.792 --> 01:15:29.007
And once you get older.

1544
01:15:29.091 --> 01:15:31.009
hopefully you will understand this.

1545
01:15:31.093 --> 01:15:32.528
Listen to yourself. Do you hear yourself

1546
01:15:32.612 --> 01:15:33.845
right now when you're talking?

1547
01:15:33.929 --> 01:15:35.921
He cheated on you. and he left you.

1548
01:15:36.005 --> 01:15:37.321
and he left all of us.

1549
01:15:37.405 --> 01:15:39.203
Why are you still defending him?

1550
01:15:39.287 --> 01:15:41.228
Because he's your father. and
you guys need your father.

1551
01:15:41.312 --> 01:15:43.268
Don't say that. This isn't about us.

1552
01:15:43.352 --> 01:15:44.595
This has never been about us.

1553
01:15:44.679 --> 01:15:46.449
- What is it about?
- You.

1554
01:15:48.987 --> 01:15:50.488
You could never let him go.

1555
01:15:50.573 --> 01:15:52.430
No matter what he did.
you forgave him for it.

1556
01:15:52.515 --> 01:15:54.517
That's not fair.

1557
01:15:56.160 --> 01:15:58.161
And it's not true. We got a divorce.

1558
01:15:58.245 --> 01:15:59.705
What more did you want from me?

1559
01:15:59.789 --> 01:16:01.274
I wanted you to condemn him.

1560
01:16:01.358 --> 01:16:03.125
I wanted you to admit to yourself

1561
01:16:03.209 --> 01:16:05.054
and to us what a shit he was.

1562
01:16:05.138 --> 01:16:07.546
so that maybe I would have an
opportunity to acknowledge

1563
01:16:07.630 --> 01:16:10.062
that that behavior wasn't normal.

1564
01:16:10.146 --> 01:16:12.175
So that maybe I wouldn't
go out looking for a guy

1565
01:16:12.259 --> 01:16:14.178
to hurt me the way that he hurt you.

1566
01:16:21.612 --> 01:16:23.120
That's what you think of me?

1567
01:16:27.979 --> 01:16:30.825
No. you don't understand.
This is all my fault.

1568
01:16:31.449 --> 01:16:33.119
None of it would have happened.

1569
01:16:33.204 --> 01:16:36.783
I mean. what those women are
saying. that's not... it's not

1570
01:16:36.867 --> 01:16:38.533
who your father is.

1571
01:16:44.299 --> 01:16:46.101
Mom. I believe them.

1572
01:16:46.185 --> 01:16:48.003
[tense music]

1573
01:16:48.087 --> 01:16:50.078
<i>♪♪♪</i>

1574
01:16:50.162 --> 01:16:52.007
He did it to me.

1575
01:16:52.091 --> 01:16:53.592
- [Noah] Whitney.
- What?

1576
01:16:54.515 --> 01:16:55.994
What are you talking about?

1577
01:16:59.265 --> 01:17:02.142
That night at Rodney Callahan's party.

1578
01:17:02.226 --> 01:17:05.353
When you got in the hot tub.
you didn't recognize me.

1579
01:17:05.438 --> 01:17:08.238
But I saw the way you look at women.

1580
01:17:12.945 --> 01:17:14.505
Like they're prey.

1581
01:17:15.032 --> 01:17:16.924
What is she talking about?

1582
01:17:18.850 --> 01:17:20.678
What is she talking about?

1583
01:17:24.992 --> 01:17:27.745
- [Helen] Noah. Noah.
- [shuddering]

1584
01:17:30.589 --> 01:17:32.481
What is she talking about?

1585
01:17:51.983 --> 01:17:59.983
